features: 🏆 REVERSIBLE SEAT & COMPACT - This RoyalBaby infant baby stroller can reorient the seat in 360°. It is ultra-compact with a quick fold & self-standing feature and can be folded while forward-facing or backward-facing. The stroller is incredibly convenient to store and easy to carry. It can easily fit in the trunk of a car for traveling or hangout in the neighborhood. The removable leather armrest is a great relief when the stroller is not needed. It is compact and can be stored in any corner of the house.

🏆 VARIOUS ADJUSTMENT FUNCTIONS - This compact folding stroller with a multi-position reclining padded backrest, adjustable from 100° to 150° providing your baby relaxing nap time while on the go. The footrest can be adjusted independently for your child to look around or nap comfortably. The stroller has a three-leveled adjustable extra-large canopy with a sun visor to protect your baby from harmful UV and a peek-a-boo window at the canopy top to observe the baby's condition.

🏆 EXTRA STORAGE - Royalbaby toddler stroller has a large basket and a multipurpose storage bag. The storage bag has multiple inner layers for heat preservation and is easy to carry. These storage spaces of this stroller can tuck in all your baby's essentials. Our stroller also includes a cup holder for drinks or bottles.

🏆 SAFE STRUCTURAL DESIGN - The seat has a 5-point adjustable harness with padded shoulder and buckle pads to provide a safe and comfortable ride. Aluminum frame construction ensures the durability of the stroller. A steady triangular weight supporting frame can support up to 33 pounds for babies 6 to 36 months. This lightweight stroller equips with one-step foot brake on rear shock-absorbent wheels, and 360 degrees front swivel wheels allows a perfect turning circle and freedom to control.

🏆 SERVICE GUARANTEE - RoyalBaby stroller is a perfect combination of functionality and compact, a breeze to use and maintain. RoyalBaby stands behind all our strollers with excellent customer service and support. If there is anything we can do to help you, please feel free to contact us at (888)881-BIKE.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 11, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good double-fold stroller if you’re short on space, but it has some wobble and is not lightweight.
reviews.reviewText: I’ve gone through a number of strollers, and our most recent strollers (a couple Britax travel systems, and a Baby Jogger double stroller) are bulky to leave in the backseat for daily use. With this stroller it seems like they started out designing an ultra-compact travel stroller and then bulked it up until it was no longer lightweight or ultra-compact. Here are my observations from using this stroller:1. It’s a multi-step fold down process. First, the seat has to be rotated to face forward. Second you have to fold the seat in half. Third, you have to fold the stroller in on itself. Finally, you need to remove the Velcro storage compartment that sits on the handles or it just flaps around.2. The seat. The seat rotates 360 on a plastic base, and it also pops right off, which is convenient for dumping crumbs and spilt snacks.3. There’s no zippered compartment. The top storage is just Velcroed on, and the main problem with it is that it keeps sliding off the handlebars. If your child sits facing you then the storage bag will slide off the handles until it rests against your child’s feet.4. Seat reclines. The seat reclines, there’s straps in the back that you loosen or tighten to adjust the seat angle.5. Front handlebar. The front handle bar / grab bar is removable. It pops right off for older toddlers so it doesn’t get in the way.6. Brakes. The brakes are on the bottom of the stroller, and lock the two back wheels. There are no hand brakes.7. Weight and size. This weighs about 20 lbs. and is as heavy, if not heavier, then our other full size single strollers. However, it only supports a child weighing up to 33 lbs. It’s more compact lengthwise when folded down for storage. If you have a SUV the size difference is not very important, but if you’re putting this in the truck of a sedan, I could imagine the double fold making a difference between fitting or not fitting.8. Turning. This glides along pretty smoothly and it’s not at all hard to turn in different directions. With other strollers using triangle design (i.e., one wheel in front, or two small wheels centered in the front) it can be hard to turn with only one hand. This has a nice four wheel / square design that makes it easy to turn the stroller. It’s also narrow enough that you don’t have problems navigating doorways.9. Durability. The main thing I don’t like about this stroller is the feel. With umbrella strollers they have this wobbly/stick feel that if you shake it the whole thing might fall apart. I’m not saying it’s that bad with this stroller, but it definitely has some of that umbrella stick/wobble feel to it. It doesn’t have the rock-solid feel of other full-size strollers. I suppose that is an element of most compact double-fold strollers. The folding elements add some wobble to it and this is a multipoint fold as opposed to a stroller where you just push one button and it collapses. I suppose that is why it only supports children weighing up to 33 lbs. For comparison, my Baby Jogger can carry my 4, 3, and 1 year old at the same time with no wobble. This one wobbles a bit with just my 1 year old in it.In summary, this is a nice and compact double-fold stroller if space is at a premium. But if you have a lot of space you might be better served with a sturdy single-fold full size stroller. The difference really is whether it matters to you that this stroller has some wobble to it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars I wanted to love it…
reviews.reviewText: I searched for WEEKS, endless hours it feels, for a stroller that was lightweight, quick to fold, parent facing option and able to lay down. I finally found this one and was so excited to get it. Everything but one thing was perfect: the recline. It reclines some but nowhere near what’s comfortable for a 6 month old to nap. She looked like a rag doll in it. I tried to push it down more to make it comfortable but no luck. I’m so sad to return it, but it just doesn’t make sense to keep it if she can’t be comfortable in it. Blah.
